\b0 \cf0 For a virtuous agent to develop virtues, she must be practically wise. She must, at least, be practical. The centrality of practical reason is one of MacIntyre\'92s recurring points. There is a close connection, he argues, between moral reasoning (narrowly about what is right and wrong) and practical reasoning (broadly about what to do). As Lutz puts it: \
