, A800/B828\'96A819/B847) and in 
\i \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The Foundations of the Metaphysics of Morals 
\i0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
(First Section, pp. 393-405.); Mill makes the same separation in 
\i \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Utilitarianism
\i0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 (chapter 2).\'94 \
Modern moral philosophers had explicitly severed the connection. But if people\'92s avowed 
\i \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
reasons for action 
\i0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
were simply a subset of their 
