\b \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The Concept of Tradition\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural

\b0 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The concept of tradition does important work for MacIntyre. A tradition is not mere conservatism of Burke or contemporary political pundits; that kind of conservatism is part of the broader tradition of liberal individualism he critiques. He calls a living tradition \'93an historically extended, socially embodied argument, and an argument precisely in part about the goods which constitute that tradition\'94 (222%). \
